Subject: [PATCH 2/6] =?UTF-8?q?phase=205=20(partial):=20pkgtools=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20Darwin=20shims=20+=20OpenSSL/pwgr=20stubs?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

WORK IN PROGRESS. Commits the Darwin compat shim layer for pkgtools
so libpkgdb.a and libpkg.a build. libadm and libinst still fail on
Darwin-native mount-table + errno / lex-generated scanner issues;
those are deferred to Phase 6 (see additions to task list).

New shim headers under pkgtools/hdrs/ (auto-included via -include
in mk.config CPPFLAGS):
    darwin_stat_shim.h    stat64/dirent64/statvfs64 -> plain, plus
                          O_LARGEFILE, ENOPKG, ECOMM, MAJOR/MINOR/
                          MAKEDEV, memalign wrapper, boolean_t via
                          <mach/mach_types.h>, and delegate to
                          darwin_pwgr_shim.h.
    darwin_pwgr_shim.h    fgetpwent/fgetgrent proto redirects.
    libintl.h             identity gettext macros (English pass-thru).
    malloc.h              delegate to <stdlib.h>.
    mntent.h + sys/mntent.h  no-op setmntent/getmntent/endmntent
                          family; MNTOPT_RO etc.
    stropts.h             STREAMS ioctl constants as 0.
    sys/sysmacros.h       delegate to <sys/types.h>.
    termio.h              delegate to <termios.h>; TCGETA aliases.
    wait.h                delegate to <sys/wait.h>.

New Darwin-native TUs:
    libpkg/darwin_pwgr.c        fgetpwent/fgetgrent impls (parse
                                colon-separated /etc/passwd|group
                                lines from a FILE*).
    libpkg/darwin_openssl_stubs.c   runtime-failing stubs for the four
                                OpenSSL-touching TUs (security.c,
                                p12lib.c, keystore.c, pkgweb.c) which
                                upstream marks as 'partially disabled'
                                and additionally don't compile against
                                OpenSSL 3.x. Any signed-package or web-
                                install code path prints a diagnostic
                                and returns ENOTSUP.
    libpkgdb/darwin_placeholder.c   single symbol so ar(1) can create
                                the semantically-empty libpkgdb.a
                                (upstream disables SQLite so OBJ is
                                empty; Darwin ar rejects zero-member).

Source patches:
    hdrs/libadm.h                skip strlcpy/strlcat/fmtcheck decls
                                 on Darwin (libc provides them).
    libadm/strlcpy.c, strlcat.c  skip body on Darwin (libc provides).
    libpkg/dbsql.c               rename 'true' local var (C23 keyword).
    libpkg/keystore.h            skip boolean_t typedef on Darwin.
    libpkg/Makefile.mk           swap OpenSSL objs for stubs; add
                                 darwin_pwgr.o and darwin_openssl_stubs.o.
    libpkgdb/Makefile.mk         swap empty OBJ for darwin_placeholder.o.
    mk.config                    inject shim via -include CPPFLAGS;
                                 LEX=/opt/heirloom/ccs/bin/lex for
                                 Bell Labs-lineage scriptvfy.l.

Every deviation carries an inline explanation citing PORT.md §
'Deviations from stock' and referencing the tracking task.
